summary:
Possible spoilers!
Honestly, though... What if Tony and Nebula aren't fixing the ship? 
What if they know they can't do anything...
body:
Possible spoilers!

Honestly, though… What if Tony and Nebula aren’t fixing the ship?

What if they know they can’t do anything to get the oxygen working or to, you know, actually get anywhere before Tony dies? But Nebula… chances are, she can survive much longer than he can without oxygen or food, given all of her implants and upgrades. So, maybe they are building a cryopod of some sort. Something to keep him alive until Nebula can get them to Earth. Maybe he is putting all his faith in Nebula, and she is so massively touched by this display that she is determined that she will not fail him.

summary: Anyway, one of my all time Tony & Peter fics is called Lazarus, come forth by iron_spider and if you haven’t read it before then...
body:
Anyway, one of my all time Tony & Peter fics is called Lazarus, come forth by iron_spider and if you haven’t read it before then wHAT are you DOING with your life go read it like riGHT NOW

Lazarus, come forth by iron_spider

Post-Infinity War, Post A4, Not Endgame Compliant, Avengers as a Family, LOTS of Tony and Peter feels, Tony comes back from the dead

Tony’s mind is a chaotic mess but he remembers the moment—remembers his death, remembers the red hot pain and Peter screaming, Rhodey rushing to his side. How he knew he’d never see Pepper again—but they’d fixed it. They’d fixed the world, erased the lost time, set things right—and the kid was back. The kid was crying, the kid hated him for doing what he did, but he was back. He was alive.

Tony Stark was dead. But now he’s breathing again, trying to think, gasping, hands tracing the box surrounding him, covering him, suffocating him.

He’s in a coffin. He’s under the ground. He’s under the fucking ground.

(Tony Stark dies defeating Thanos. But then he comes back to life. He has to find out how, why, and how to live again. And how to deal with the changes in the people he’s coming back to.)
